{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1575,"text":"I'd like to start with a simple question:"},{"time":6000,"text":"Why do the poor make\nso many poor decisions?"},{"time":11852,"text":"I know it's a harsh question,"},{"time":13427,"text":"but take a look at the data."},{"time":15416,"text":"The poor borrow more, save less,"},{"time":17283,"text":"smoke more, exercise less, drink more"},{"time":19966,"text":"and eat less healthfully."},{"time":22372,"text":"Why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":24451,"text":"Well, the standard explanation"},{"time":26002,"text":"was once summed up by the British\nPrime Minister, Margaret Thatcher."},{"time":29406,"text":"And she called poverty\n\"a personality defect.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":32815,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34679,"text":"A lack of character, basically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37465,"text":"Now, I'm sure not many of you\nwould be so blunt."},{"time":42497,"text":"But the idea that there's something\nwrong with the poor themselves"},{"time":46371,"text":"is not restricted to Mrs. Thatcher."},{"time":49285,"text":"Some of you may believe that the poor\nshould be held responsible"},{"time":52512,"text":"for their own mistakes."},{"time":54289,"text":"And others may argue that we should\nhelp them to make better decisions."},{"time":58854,"text":"But the underlying assumption is the same:"},{"time":62650,"text":"there's something wrong with them."},{"time":66057,"text":"If we could just change them,"},{"time":67939,"text":"if we could just teach them\nhow to live their lives,"},{"time":70455,"text":"if they would only listen."},{"time":73233,"text":"And to be honest,"},{"time":74954,"text":"this was what I thought for a long time."},{"time":79078,"text":"It was only a few years ago\nthat I discovered"},{"time":81216,"text":"that everything I thought I knew\nabout poverty was wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86286,"text":"It all started when I accidentally\nstumbled upon a paper"},{"time":88961,"text":"by a few American psychologists."},{"time":90593,"text":"They had traveled 8,000 miles,\nall the way to India,"},{"time":93170,"text":"for a fascinating study."},{"time":95245,"text":"And it was an experiment\nwith sugarcane farmers."},{"time":98838,"text":"You should know that these farmers\ncollect about 60 percent"},{"time":102210,"text":"of their annual income all at once,"},{"time":104367,"text":"right after the harvest."},{"time":106099,"text":"This means that they're relatively\npoor one part of the year"},{"time":109663,"text":"and rich the other."},{"time":112595,"text":"The researchers asked them to do\nan IQ test before and after the harvest."},{"time":117902,"text":"What they subsequently discovered\ncompletely blew my mind."},{"time":123159,"text":"The farmers scored much worse\non the test before the harvest."},{"time":128457,"text":"The effects of living\nin poverty, it turns out,"},{"time":130781,"text":"correspond to losing 14 points of IQ."},{"time":134173,"text":"Now, to give you an idea,"},{"time":136066,"text":"that's comparable\nto losing a night's sleep"},{"time":138531,"text":"or the effects of alcoholism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142685,"text":"A few months later,\nI heard that Eldar Shafir,"},{"time":144968,"text":"a professor at Princeton University\nand one of the authors of this study,"},{"time":148539,"text":"was coming over to Holland, where I live."},{"time":150882,"text":"So we met up in Amsterdam"},{"time":152308,"text":"to talk about his revolutionary\nnew theory of poverty."},{"time":156390,"text":"And I can sum it up in just two words:"},{"time":159415,"text":"scarcity mentality."},{"time":162647,"text":"It turns out that people\nbehave differently"},{"time":164825,"text":"when they perceive a thing to be scarce."},{"time":167335,"text":"And what that thing is\ndoesn't much matter --"},{"time":169574,"text":"whether it's not enough time,\nmoney or food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173080,"text":"You all know this feeling,"},{"time":174762,"text":"when you've got too much to do,"},{"time":176749,"text":"or when you've put off breaking for lunch"},{"time":178789,"text":"and your blood sugar takes a dive."},{"time":180476,"text":"This narrows your focus\nto your immediate lack --"},{"time":183328,"text":"to the sandwich you've got to have now,"},{"time":185362,"text":"the meeting that's starting\nin five minutes"},{"time":187648,"text":"or the bills that have\nto be paid tomorrow."},{"time":191048,"text":"So the long-term perspective\ngoes out the window."},{"time":195835,"text":"You could compare it to a new computer"},{"time":198390,"text":"that's running 10 heavy programs at once."},{"time":201201,"text":"It gets slower and slower, making errors."},{"time":203998,"text":"Eventually, it freezes --"},{"time":205844,"text":"not because it's a bad computer,"},{"time":207974,"text":"but because it has too much to do at once."},{"time":211459,"text":"The poor have the same problem."},{"time":214834,"text":"They're not making dumb decisions\nbecause they are dumb,"},{"time":217648,"text":"but because they're living in a context"},{"time":219594,"text":"in which anyone would make dumb decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222542,"text":"So suddenly I understood"},{"time":225514,"text":"why so many of our anti-poverty\nprograms don't work."},{"time":230647,"text":"Investments in education, for example,\nare often completely ineffective."},{"time":235195,"text":"Poverty is not a lack of knowledge."},{"time":238760,"text":"A recent analysis of 201 studies"},{"time":241339,"text":"on the effectiveness\nof money-management training"},{"time":243675,"text":"came to the conclusion\nthat it has almost no effect at all."},{"time":247448,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong --"},{"time":248917,"text":"this is not to say the poor\ndon't learn anything --"},{"time":251437,"text":"they can come out wiser for sure."},{"time":254012,"text":"But it's not enough."},{"time":255674,"text":"Or as Professor Shafir told me,"},{"time":258700,"text":"\"It's like teaching someone to swim"},{"time":260708,"text":"and then throwing them in a stormy sea.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":264688,"text":"I still remember sitting there,"},{"time":267203,"text":"perplexed."},{"time":269291,"text":"And it struck me"},{"time":270472,"text":"that we could have figured\nthis all out decades ago."},{"time":273009,"text":"I mean, these psychologists didn't need\nany complicated brain scans;"},{"time":276284,"text":"they only had to measure the farmer's IQ,"},{"time":278317,"text":"and IQ tests were invented\nmore than 100 years ago."},{"time":281219,"text":"Actually, I realized I had read about\nthe psychology of poverty before."},{"time":285547,"text":"George Orwell, one of the greatest\nwriters who ever lived,"},{"time":289245,"text":"experienced poverty\nfirsthand in the 1920s."},{"time":292856,"text":"\"The essence of poverty,\"\nhe wrote back then,"},{"time":295058,"text":"is that it \"annihilates the future.\""},{"time":299147,"text":"And he marveled at, quote,"},{"time":301926,"text":"\"How people take it for granted\nthey have the right to preach at you"},{"time":305236,"text":"and pray over you"},{"time":306411,"text":"as soon as your income falls\nbelow a certain level.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":308907,"text":"Now, those words are every bit\nas resonant today."},{"time":315145,"text":"The big question is, of course:"},{"time":317150,"text":"What can be done?"},{"time":318514,"text":"Modern economists have\na few solutions up their sleeves."},{"time":321333,"text":"We could help the poor\nwith their paperwork"},{"time":323416,"text":"or send them a text message\nto remind them to pay their bills."},{"time":326422,"text":"This type of solution is hugely popular\nwith modern politicians,"},{"time":331153,"text":"mostly because,"},{"time":332880,"text":"well, they cost next to nothing."},{"time":336135,"text":"These solutions are, I think,\na symbol of this era"},{"time":340169,"text":"in which we so often treat the symptoms,"},{"time":342370,"text":"but ignore the underlying cause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345674,"text":"So I wonder:"},{"time":347786,"text":"Why don't we just change the context\nin which the poor live?"},{"time":351725,"text":"Or, going back to our computer analogy:"},{"time":353874,"text":"Why keep tinkering around\nwith the software"},{"time":356035,"text":"when we can easily solve the problem\nby installing some extra memory instead?"},{"time":360124,"text":"At that point, Professor Shafir\nresponded with a blank look."},{"time":364292,"text":"And after a few seconds, he said,"},{"time":366922,"text":"\"Oh, I get it."},{"time":369660,"text":"You mean you want to just hand out\nmore money to the poor"},{"time":374144,"text":"to eradicate poverty."},{"time":376019,"text":"Uh, sure, that'd be great."},{"time":379914,"text":"But I'm afraid that brand\nof left-wing politics"},{"time":382239,"text":"you've got in Amsterdam --"},{"time":384107,"text":"it doesn't exist in the States.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":386522,"text":"But is this really\nan old-fashioned, leftist idea?"},{"time":391394,"text":"I remembered reading about an old plan --"},{"time":393405,"text":"something that has been proposed\nby some of history's leading thinkers."},{"time":396913,"text":"The philosopher Thomas More\nfirst hinted at it in his book, \"Utopia,\""},{"time":400753,"text":"more than 500 years ago."},{"time":403205,"text":"And its proponents have spanned\nthe spectrum from the left to the right,"},{"time":406779,"text":"from the civil rights campaigner,\nMartin Luther King,"},{"time":409573,"text":"to the economist Milton Friedman."},{"time":413273,"text":"And it's an incredibly simple idea:"},{"time":417243,"text":"basic income guarantee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421465,"text":"What it is?"},{"time":423004,"text":"Well, that's easy."},{"time":424727,"text":"It's a monthly grant, enough to pay\nfor your basic needs:"},{"time":427482,"text":"food, shelter, education."},{"time":429683,"text":"It's completely unconditional,"},{"time":431528,"text":"so no one's going to tell you\nwhat you have to do for it,"},{"time":434312,"text":"and no one's going to tell you\nwhat you have to do with it."},{"time":437154,"text":"The basic income\nis not a favor, but a right."},{"time":439468,"text":"There's absolutely no stigma attached."},{"time":442372,"text":"So as I learned about the true\nnature of poverty,"},{"time":445026,"text":"I couldn't stop wondering:"},{"time":447208,"text":"Is this the idea\nwe've all been waiting for?"},{"time":450698,"text":"Could it really be that simple?"},{"time":454348,"text":"And in the three years that followed,"},{"time":456172,"text":"I read everything I could find\nabout basic income."},{"time":458734,"text":"I researched the dozens of experiments"},{"time":460695,"text":"that have been conducted\nall over the globe,"},{"time":462840,"text":"and it didn't take long before I stumbled\nupon a story of a town"},{"time":465932,"text":"that had done it --\nhad actually eradicated poverty."},{"time":468428,"text":"But then ..."},{"time":470478,"text":"nearly everyone forgot about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473586,"text":"This story starts in Dauphin, Canada."},{"time":477051,"text":"In 1974, everybody in this small town\nwas guaranteed a basic income,"},{"time":482655,"text":"ensuring that no one fell\nbelow the poverty line."},{"time":485414,"text":"At the start of the experiment,"},{"time":487034,"text":"an army of researchers\ndescended on the town."},{"time":491367,"text":"For four years, all went well."},{"time":494511,"text":"But then a new government\nwas voted into power,"},{"time":497967,"text":"and the new Canadian cabinet saw\nlittle point to the expensive experiment."},{"time":501501,"text":"So when it became clear there was\nno money left to analyze the results,"},{"time":505778,"text":"the researchers decided to pack\ntheir files away in some 2,000 boxes."},{"time":512175,"text":"Twenty-five years went by,"},{"time":514989,"text":"and then Evelyn Forget,\na Canadian professor,"},{"time":517701,"text":"found the records."},{"time":518941,"text":"For three years, she subjected the data\nto all manner of statistical analysis,"},{"time":522932,"text":"and no matter what she tried,"},{"time":524542,"text":"the results were the same every time:"},{"time":527968,"text":"the experiment had been\na resounding success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533311,"text":"Evelyn Forget discovered"},{"time":534495,"text":"that the people in Dauphin\nhad not only become richer"},{"time":537103,"text":"but also smarter and healthier."},{"time":538658,"text":"The school performance of kids\nimproved substantially."},{"time":543156,"text":"The hospitalization rate decreased\nby as much as 8.5 percent."},{"time":548122,"text":"Domestic violence incidents were down,"},{"time":549956,"text":"as were mental health complaints."},{"time":552153,"text":"And people didn't quit their jobs."},{"time":554509,"text":"The only ones who worked a little less\nwere new mothers and students --"},{"time":558267,"text":"who stayed in school longer."},{"time":560888,"text":"Similar results have since been found"},{"time":562787,"text":"in countless other experiments\naround the globe,"},{"time":565207,"text":"from the US to India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569613,"text":"So ..."},{"time":571680,"text":"here's what I've learned."},{"time":573995,"text":"When it comes to poverty,"},{"time":576175,"text":"we, the rich, should stop\npretending we know best."},{"time":582211,"text":"We should stop sending shoes\nand teddy bears to the poor,"},{"time":584989,"text":"to people we have never met."},{"time":586534,"text":"And we should get rid of the vast\nindustry of paternalistic bureaucrats"},{"time":590091,"text":"when we could simply\nhand over their salaries"},{"time":592296,"text":"to the poor they're supposed to help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594126,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596446,"text":"Because, I mean, the great\nthing about money"},{"time":599343,"text":"is that people can use it\nto buy things they need"},{"time":601718,"text":"instead of things that self-appointed\nexperts think they need."},{"time":605882,"text":"Just imagine how many brilliant scientists\nand entrepreneurs and writers,"},{"time":610310,"text":"like George Orwell,"},{"time":611485,"text":"are now withering away in scarcity."},{"time":614299,"text":"Imagine how much energy\nand talent we would unleash"},{"time":616779,"text":"if we got rid of poverty once and for all."},{"time":619542,"text":"I believe that a basic income would work\nlike venture capital for the people."},{"time":625093,"text":"And we can't afford not to do it,"},{"time":627161,"text":"because poverty is hugely expensive."},{"time":630546,"text":"Just look at the cost of child poverty\nin the US, for example."},{"time":633962,"text":"It's estimated at 500 billion\ndollars each year,"},{"time":638218,"text":"in terms of higher health care\nspending, higher dropout rates,"},{"time":641190,"text":"and more crime."},{"time":642597,"text":"Now, this is an incredible waste\nof human potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648365,"text":"But let's talk about\nthe elephant in the room."},{"time":651326,"text":"How could we ever afford\na basic income guarantee?"},{"time":655052,"text":"Well, it's actually a lot cheaper\nthan you may think."},{"time":658175,"text":"What they did in Dauphin is finance it\nwith a negative income tax."},{"time":661763,"text":"This means that your income is topped up"},{"time":663795,"text":"as soon as you fall\nbelow the poverty line."},{"time":666231,"text":"And in that scenario,"},{"time":667617,"text":"according to our economists'\nbest estimates,"},{"time":670155,"text":"for a net cost of 175 billion --"},{"time":673204,"text":"a quarter of US military spending,\none percent of GDP --"},{"time":678135,"text":"you could lift all impoverished Americans\nabove the poverty line."},{"time":682566,"text":"You could actually eradicate poverty."},{"time":686142,"text":"Now, that should be our goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688716,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":689824,"text":"The time for small thoughts\nand little nudges is past."},{"time":692780,"text":"I really believe that the time has come\nfor radical new ideas,"},{"time":696112,"text":"and basic income is so much more\nthan just another policy."},{"time":699336,"text":"It is also a complete rethink\nof what work actually is."},{"time":703998,"text":"And in that sense,"},{"time":705692,"text":"it will not only free the poor,"},{"time":708532,"text":"but also the rest of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711261,"text":"Nowadays, millions of people feel"},{"time":713531,"text":"that their jobs have little\nmeaning or significance."},{"time":716061,"text":"A recent poll among 230,000 employees"},{"time":718902,"text":"in 142 countries"},{"time":720832,"text":"found that only 13 percent of workers\nactually like their job."},{"time":726600,"text":"And another poll found that as much\nas 37 percent of British workers"},{"time":730291,"text":"have a job that they think\ndoesn't even need to exist."},{"time":734387,"text":"It's like Brad Pitt says in \"Fight Club,\""},{"time":736705,"text":"\"Too often we're working jobs we hate\nso we can buy shit we don't need.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":740385,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":741887,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong --"},{"time":743308,"text":"I'm not talking about the teachers\nand the garbagemen"},{"time":745886,"text":"and the care workers here."},{"time":747392,"text":"If they stopped working,"},{"time":749030,"text":"we'd be in trouble."},{"time":750990,"text":"I'm talking about all those well-paid\nprofessionals with excellent résumés"},{"time":754639,"text":"who earn their money doing ..."},{"time":756468,"text":"strategic transactor peer-to-peer meetings"},{"time":758528,"text":"while brainstorming the value\nadd-on of disruptive co-creation"},{"time":761584,"text":"in the network society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762781,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":763828,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764870,"text":"Or something like that."},{"time":766096,"text":"Just imagine again how much\ntalent we're wasting,"},{"time":769044,"text":"simply because we tell our kids\nthey'll have to \"earn a living.\""},{"time":773638,"text":"Or think of what a math whiz working\nat Facebook lamented a few years ago:"},{"time":777404,"text":"\"The best minds of my generation"},{"time":779290,"text":"are thinking about how\nto make people click ads.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":784699,"text":"I'm a historian."},{"time":786992,"text":"And if history teaches us anything,"},{"time":789085,"text":"it is that things could be different."},{"time":791901,"text":"There is nothing inevitable"},{"time":793316,"text":"about the way we structured our society\nand economy right now."},{"time":796297,"text":"Ideas can and do change the world."},{"time":798677,"text":"And I think that especially\nin the past few years,"},{"time":801212,"text":"it has become abundantly clear"},{"time":802665,"text":"that we cannot stick to the status quo --"},{"time":804642,"text":"that we need new ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808499,"text":"I know that many of you\nmay feel pessimistic"},{"time":811736,"text":"about a future of rising inequality,"},{"time":813823,"text":"xenophobia"},{"time":815124,"text":"and climate change."},{"time":816986,"text":"But it's not enough\nto know what we're against."},{"time":819228,"text":"We also need to be for something."},{"time":820864,"text":"Martin Luther King didn't say,\n\"I have a nightmare.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":823422,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":825319,"text":"He had a dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826502,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":827605,"text":"So ..."},{"time":829835,"text":"here's my dream:"},{"time":832303,"text":"I believe in a future"},{"time":833965,"text":"where the value of your work\nis not determined"},{"time":836342,"text":"by the size of your paycheck,"},{"time":837843,"text":"but by the amount of happiness you spread"},{"time":839899,"text":"and the amount of meaning you give."},{"time":841900,"text":"I believe in a future"},{"time":843156,"text":"where the point of education is not\nto prepare you for another useless job"},{"time":846840,"text":"but for a life well-lived."},{"time":849204,"text":"I believe in a future"},{"time":850507,"text":"where an existence\nwithout poverty is not a privilege"},{"time":853625,"text":"but a right we all deserve."},{"time":855662,"text":"So here we are."},{"time":857151,"text":"Here we are."},{"time":858326,"text":"We've got the research,\nwe've got the evidence"},{"time":860540,"text":"and we've got the means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861727,"text":"Now, more than 500 years after Thomas More\nfirst wrote about a basic income,"},{"time":865660,"text":"and 100 years after George Orwell\ndiscovered the true nature of poverty,"},{"time":869739,"text":"we all need to change our worldview,"},{"time":872204,"text":"because poverty\nis not a lack of character."},{"time":875832,"text":"Poverty is a lack of cash."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879321,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880529,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}